Quick guide to building the resiprocate and dum libraries and tests:
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Unpack the distribution, cd to the sip directory
$ ./configure
$ make


Try ./configure --help to see what the configurable options are.
There are many - the most interesting are:

  --enable-ssl              Enable use of SSL [default=yes]
  --enable-distcc           compile in parallel with distcc
  --enable-ipv6             use IPv6 code [default=no]
  --enable-google-malloc    use Google malloc [default=no]
  --enable-google-cpuperf   use Google cpuperf [default=no]
  --enable-boost            use BOOST [default=no]
  --enable-curl             use CURL [default=no]
  --enable-scanner-debug    use new message scanner debug
  --enable-elog             enable log calls inside exceptions
  --enable-data-local-size  Define localAlloc size [default 16]


To build with distcc for distributed compilation  - See http://distcc.samba.org/
  (assume you have 4 hosts runing distccd)
% ./configure --with-distcc
% make -j 8   

